1
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:24,375
[CANA]
What is this... this light?

2
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:27,625
It's like fire
Am I seeing things?

3
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:30,666
And this rain?

4
00:00:36,458 --> 00:00:41,458
♪

5
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:12,125
This light is intense.
Is it magic power?

6
00:02:16,958 --> 00:02:18,000
[CANA shouting]

7
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:28,458
"Here I seal Fairy Glitter, one
of the Three Grand Fairy spells.

8
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:30,625
May it forever shine
in the darkness."

9
00:02:31,916 --> 00:02:33,500
This isn't her grave at all!

10
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,458
[HAPPY]
The One Thing I Couldn't Say

11
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:49,250
Alright, jerk wad.
What exactly are you after?!

12
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,375
[BLUENOTE] As I said
before, I want to know

13
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:54,916
the location of Mavis
Vermillion's resting place.

14
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,583
You'll be looking for a while
'cause we don't know either!

15
00:02:57,666 --> 00:02:59,833
I wonder what he wants
with Master Mavis.

16
00:02:59,916 --> 00:03:01,250
Do you think it may have
something to do with

17
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,041
the second part of the trial?

18
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:05,250
I think I just
figured out what he's after!

19
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,791
I'm sure we'll end up
dumber once we hear

20
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:09,583
what you have to say but,
by all means, go ahead.

21
00:03:09,666 --> 00:03:12,208
Mr. Crazy Pony Tail wants
to be an S-Class wizard too,

22
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:14,000
so he came out here
to make us accept him

23
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:15,500
as a member of the guild!

24
00:03:15,583 --> 00:03:17,041
There go my brain cells.

25
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:19,416
No, Happy!

26
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,000
[BLUENOTE]
All right, that's enough!

27
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:25,083
No more comments from you. I'll
say this once, so listen well.

28
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:27,875
I don't know anything about a
'trial' and I have no intention

29
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:30,000
of joining you pathetic fools.

30
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:32,000
[LUCY]
The only fool I see here is you!

31
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,583
[WENDY]
Lucy, stop it!

32
00:03:33,666 --> 00:03:36,458
Her grave is more than just a
headstone it's sacred ground!

33
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:39,708
Even if we knew where it was,
we'd never tell someone like...

34
00:03:40,458 --> 00:03:43,291
What do you want!
Tell me!

35
00:03:43,375 --> 00:03:48,750
I want the sparkle
of faeries. Fairy Glitter.

36
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:51,750
One of your guild's
Three Grand Spells.

37
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:55,750
'just as powerful, if not
more so, than Fairy Law itself.

38
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:59,583
[NATSU] Is glitter all you want?
Try hittin' up a craft store!

39
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:00,750
[LUCY and WENDY]
Natsu!

40
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,791
[NATSU]
Ow! I'm a human pancake!

41
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:04,750
[BLUENOTE] I want
that merciless light.

42
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:07,916
Tell me where to find it or
I'll squash you until you pop.

43
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,083
Like we'd tell you.

44
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,291
Stay strong, you can
push through this!

45
00:04:12,375 --> 00:04:15,458
Which of your friends would
you like to see crushed first?

46
00:04:15,541 --> 00:04:19,750
I'm Natsu Dragneel...
I'm the son of Igneel!

47
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,166
It'll take more

48
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,375
than you've got to keep me
pinned to the ground, pal!

49
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:27,541
[NATSU]
I won't be defeated so easily!

50
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:28,625
He's running!

51
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:31,666
Wow. Under that
much gravity? Amazing!

52
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:35,375
I hear it was sealed away
with Mavis when she was buried.

53
00:04:35,458 --> 00:04:37,875
Tell me where it is
and I'll leave you alone.

54
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:40,833
He jumped!

55
00:04:40,916 --> 00:04:42,375
He seriously hates losin', huh?

56
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:44,666
Fire Dragon Iron--

57
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:50,833
You should listen when
someone's talking to you.

58
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,375
Natsu!

59
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:56,625
He's down.

60
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,625
Great.

61
00:04:58,708 --> 00:04:59,916
What'll we do?

62
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,666
We can't touch him!

63
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:07,291
[BLUENOTE] I see you've
brought Mahkarov...

64
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,458
Perfect. I'll just
ask him where it is.

65
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:15,041
[NATSU] No you won't! Mess with
Gramps and I'll roast you alive!

66
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:16,500
We're not done talkin'

67
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:22,041
[BLUENOTE] We're done talking
when I say we're done.

68
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:23,708
Now are you going to
be helpful or should I

69
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:25,958
squash you all flat? Well?

70
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:28,500
[CARLA] This brute is
way too strong for us!

71
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:32,833
[WENDY] This is bad. He's got
us completely stuck here!

72
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,041
[LUCY]
Someone. Help us!

73
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:43,041
[CANA] What is this?
Some sort of sick joke!

74
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:47,750
I'm looking for a grave,
not some stupid spell!

75
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:50,166
How am I supposed
to finish the trial!

76
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:53,083
Master. I need answers!

77
00:05:56,750 --> 00:06:01,458
Am I just not good enough
to become an S-Class wizard?

78
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:02,791
After everything
that's happened,

79
00:06:02,875 --> 00:06:06,375
I fall short at the finish line.

80
00:06:06,458 --> 00:06:07,625
Have the past twelve years

81
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:11,625
of my life been nothing
but a big waste of time?

82
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:19,791
[whimpering]

83
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:23,000
[CANA] On a rainy day
twelve years ago,

84
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:25,083
my mother passed away.

85
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:26,333
When her will was read,

86
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:28,708
I learned that
my father was still alive.

87
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:33,708
So I set out on my own to
look for him and found myself

88
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:35,833
at Fairy Tail's front door.

89
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:44,250
All I knew about him
was his name... Gildarts.

90
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:51,458
Hey, little lady. What are you
doing in a place like this?

91
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:52,541
Uh.

92
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,208
[CANA]
It's my daddy!

93
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,083
[GILDARTS]
You should hurry back home.

94
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,541
If you keep hangin' around
your clothes will start reekin'

95
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:02,250
of booze in no time flat.

96
00:07:02,333 --> 00:07:07,875
[CANA] Wait, Daddy. Come back!
How come you don't recognize me?

97
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:12,166
I didn't get
to tell you about mom.

98
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:20,250
Who's the half-pint?
You lost kiddo?

99
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:23,041
You shouldn't be hangin' around
a rowdy place like this.

100
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:26,666
'Scuse me. Do you know when
Mr. Gildarts is gonna come back?

101
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:29,291
Gildarts, huh? Why're you
lookin' for a chump like him?

102
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:30,541
He break your heart?

103
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:32,333
I need to see him.

104
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,208
He just left on
a job today, didn't he?

105
00:07:35,291 --> 00:07:37,375
[WAKABA] Yeah, sounded like a
tough one. He could be gone

106
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:40,583
a few days or as long as
month. Hard to say, really.

107
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:43,541
[MACAO] Awww, Don't worry!
He'll be back sooner or later!

108
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:45,750
[WAKABA] Come in and have
some juice. Our treat!

109
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:52,208
[CANA] I came back to the guild
so many times waiting for

110
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:55,125
my father to return,
that I eventually ended up

111
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,083
joining Fairy Tail.

112
00:07:57,166 --> 00:08:06,833
[bells ringing, ground shaking]

113
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,833
Why is the city breaking!

114
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:14,875
This is what happens when
Gildarts comes back to Magnolia.

115
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,541
Two months of waiting
has finally paid off!

116
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:20,541
[CANA]
But then.

117
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,458
Wow! You look terrible!

118
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:25,583
[GILDARTS]
Nice to see you too, Master.

119
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:28,125
[MAKAROV] I guess the job was
rougher than we expected.

120
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,625
But the client was pleased;

121
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:32,083
they already sent a thank you
letter by carrier pigeon.

122
00:08:32,166 --> 00:08:33,916
[GILDARTS]
Really? Glad to hear it.

123
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,583
[WAKABA]
Welcome back, Gildarts!

124
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:38,458
[MACAO] Do ya Got a minute?
We'd like you to meet someone.

125
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:41,541
[MAKAROV] Oh that's right, where
are my manners? This is Cana,

126
00:08:41,625 --> 00:08:44,375
our newest member.
She's very excited to meet you.

127
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:46,333
Uh. Hello!

128
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:51,375
Cana? You know. You look
awfully familiar to me.

129
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:54,583
Wait, I remember you now!
You were that girl standing by

130
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:57,208
the entrance when I left
for the last job, right?

131
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:58,666
So you've joined up, huh?

132
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:01,375
Well glad to have you aboard,
little lady. Work hard!

133
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,708
I need to tell you.

134
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:06,416
Sorry, I know
you've just returned

135
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,875
but if you have a moment.

136
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,625
I have something to discuss.

137
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:13,750
[GILDARTS] You're kidding me.
What is it this time?

138
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:17,000
[CANA] Sometimes my father
wouldn't come back for months.

139
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,708
When he did, he'd turn
right around and leave

140
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,416
for another job.

141
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:24,750
[GILDARTS]
Yo.

142
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:27,791
You're sproutin'
like a bean stalk, Cana!

143
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:30,541
[CANA]
Uh. By the way.

144
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:33,416
Get a move on, or the train
is going to leave without you.

145
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:37,083
Uh oh! Catch ya later, Cana!

146
00:09:37,166 --> 00:09:39,291
[CANA]
Later, Dad.

147
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:42,875
[CANA] The one thing I couldn't
say eventually became

148
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:45,375
a crushing weight
I couldn't ignore.

149
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:51,750
I learned how to read
fortune-telling cards

150
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:55,333
so I could predict when my
father would make it back home.

151
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:57,583
Hey. When did
ya learn to read those?

152
00:09:57,666 --> 00:10:00,083
You been hidin' under a rock?
Cana's a natural,

153
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,875
all her predictions
have been spot on.

154
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:04,041
Wow! If you enjoy it,

155
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:06,625
then maybe you should think
about learning some Card magic.

156
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:09,583
The ol' wino's actually got
some good advice now and then.

157
00:10:09,666 --> 00:10:12,958
You think I could
learn? Honestly?

158
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:16,583
But how do I even
begin to learn magic?

159
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:19,541
[MAKAROV] With your heart. If
you want to learn, you have to

160
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:22,166
believe in your heart
that you can learn.

161
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:23,708
Like with your fortunetelling.

162
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:26,708
You have faith that what you
predict will come to pass.

163
00:10:26,791 --> 00:10:29,708
Learning to use magic requires
the same faith and hard work

164
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:32,208
as any other useful skill.

165
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:35,000
If you can believe in
the way of the natural world,

166
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:38,708
trust in yourself, and learn
to live in harmony with both,

167
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:42,625
you will easily master
the power of magic.

168
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:45,833
Just let your heart
be your guide.

169
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:47,750
My heart.

170
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:52,791
[CANA] The very next day, I
started learning card magic.

171
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:55,125
I took to it like
a fish to water.

172
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:58,958
Hoping that mastering it would
somehow bring me closer to him.

173
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:00,375
But it didn't.

174
00:11:00,458 --> 00:11:02,750
My father was
the guild's best wizard.

175
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,083
He was placed on a pedestal,

176
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,291
and everyone down below
basked in his radiance.

177
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:11,083
I was buried beneath them;
out of sight and out of mind.

178
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:16,958
Years went by, and I still
never told him who I was.

179
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:19,083
I started to fear telling him.

180
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:20,666
What if he rejected me?

181
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,916
What if I wasn't good enough?

182
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,750
Then they announced the
candidates for that years'

183
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:28,000
S-Class Promotion Trial.

184
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:30,583
[CANA]
Master chose me?

185
00:11:30,666 --> 00:11:32,375
[GILDARTS]
I'm rooting for ya!

186
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:38,541
[CANA]
I decided then.

187
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:40,333
I would tell
my father the truth,

188
00:11:40,416 --> 00:11:43,125
when I became an
S-Class wizard like him.

189
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:53,750
But for four years in a row
now, I've only known defeat.

190
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,875
Even Erza and Mira, who
joined the guild after I did,

191
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:59,750
managed to become S-Class.

192
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,875
I'm nothing but a failure.

193
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:07,000
My father could never
be proud of me as I am.

194
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:10,625
That's why I decided
to make this my last attempt.

195
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:12,000
Alright, then.

196
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:14,750
I've been seriously
considering quitting the guild.

197
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:19,000
[CANA]
Do you understand?

198
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:21,416
I have to be an S-Class
wizard or I'll never be able

199
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,375
to look him in the eye.

200
00:12:23,458 --> 00:12:27,541
That's why this is my last one.
If I fail, I'll leave for good.

201
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:32,291
Cana, will you please
let me be your partner?

202
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:34,708
Fairy Tail just wouldn't
be the same without you.

203
00:12:34,791 --> 00:12:38,000
I promise I can help you
become an S-Class wizard!

204
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:43,458
[alarm]

205
00:12:43,541 --> 00:12:45,375
Help! Help! Help!

206
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:47,875
[LUCY]
So, what's with the card?

207
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:50,083
[CANA] Don't lose it.
If you're ever it trouble,

208
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:52,416
that'll let me know immediately.

209
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:56,875
The card I have will start
shining and lead me back to you.

210
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,875
No matter how far apart we are.

211
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:04,250
[alarm]

212
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:12,250
Help! Help! Help!

213
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:20,708
[CANA]
What have I done? Lucy, I...

214
00:13:20,791 --> 00:13:34,916
[CANA crying]

215
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:39,750
[CANA] No! It wasn't
supposed to be like this!

216
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:44,000
I never meant to
betray my friends.

217
00:13:44,083 --> 00:13:47,666
I can't do this anymore.

218
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:50,250
[CANA crying]

219
00:13:57,583 --> 00:14:01,291
[CANA] It's okay if I don't
become an S-Class wizard.

220
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:05,000
It's okay if I never
tell my father the truth.

221
00:14:05,083 --> 00:14:08,083
As much as I want that.

222
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:10,666
I want to protect
my friends even more!

223
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:17,500
'Please! I have to save them.

224
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:19,750
That's my only
purpose right now!

225
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:22,416
It doesn't matter whether
I stay in the guild or not!

226
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:24,791
Because no matter
where I end up,

227
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:30,000
or who I become, my heart will
always belong to Fairy Tail!

228
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:34,666
I'm begging you.

229
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:36,041
I need the power.

230
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:38,666
And you're the only one
who can give it to me now!

231
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:42,708
I can't do it alone!

232
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:51,125
Give me the strength...

233
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:54,416
...to protect the guild and
family that I hold dear.

234
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:04,875
[FEMALE VOICE] Dry your eyes.
You have nothing to fear.

235
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:23,250
[CANA]
Could it be her?

236
00:15:31,041 --> 00:15:32,458
Master Mavis.

237
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:35,583
Right!

238
00:15:39,791 --> 00:15:42,916
I could be running straight
to my death, but I don't care.

239
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:47,250
I've got twelve years
of kindness to repay.

240
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,458
And you better believe
I'm gonna deliver!

241
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,416
